The paper deals with 3D objectness estimation, which is a task related to computer vision (CV). The proposed method involves iterative grouping of 3D segments, which can be seen as a robotics (RO) problem. The regret mechanism used in the method involves learning from mistakes, which is a common theme in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper deals with 3D scene understanding, which can be categorized under computer graphics (GR). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.GR.
